{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a052d78d-b843-4176-b4e9-ae78f111af34","content":"Since I don't have your repository checked out, here's general guidance for MCP skill evaluations:\n\n## Evaluation Format (`evaluation.yml`)\n\nEvaluations are typically YAML files with questions that test tool usage:\n\n```yaml\nquestions:\n  - question: \"What is the price of the 'Wireless Mouse X200'?\"\n    expectations:\n      - The response includes the correct price\n      - The search_products or get_product tool was called\n    tools_expected:\n      - search_products\n\n  - question: \"Compare the top-rated keyboards under $50\"\n    expectations:\n      - Multiple products are returned and compared\n      - Filtering by category and price was applied\n    tools_expected:\n      - search_products\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n**1. Single-tool basics** — Can the LLM pick the right tool?\n> *\"Find all products in the 'Audio' category\"*\n\n**2. Multi-tool chaining** — Can it compose tool calls?\n> *\"Which product in the 'Peripherals' category has the best reviews?\"*\n\n**3. Parameter extraction** — Can it map natural language to tool params?\n> *\"Show me wireless mice under $30 sorted by rating\"*\n\n**4. Ambiguity handling** — Does it clarify or make reasonable assumptions?\n> *\"Find the cheapest one\"* (no category specified)\n\n**5. Edge cases** — How does it handle no-results or errors?\n> *\"Find products from the 'Spaceship' category\"*\n\n## Tips\n- **Be specific in expectations** — assert on tool names called, key facts in the answer, and correct parameter values\n- **Cover each tool** — ensure every tool your server exposes is tested by at least one question\n- **Mix difficulty** — include straightforward lookups alongside multi-step reasoning\n- **Test refusal** — include questions outside the tool's scope to verify the LLM doesn't hallucinate\n\nWant me to scaffold an `evaluation.yml` file for your specific tools? If so, share your tool definitions and I'll generate it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4a5a894f-7e4e-436d-97b0-4c5d8a3b1a85","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and there's no repository checked out. The user is asking a general guidance question about evaluation format for MCP server skills. Let me provide guidance based on the skill-validator evaluation format that's described in the repository instructions.\n\nSince I don't have the actual repository to reference, I'll provide general guidance about evaluation YAML format for MCP/skill evaluations based on what I know about the skill-validator format.\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n- Evaluations are defined in `evaluation.yml` files\n- They test how well an LLM uses MCP tools\n- The skill-validator validates these evaluations\n\nI should give practical, useful guidance about the evaluation format and best practices for writing good evaluation questions, even though I don't have the specific repo files to reference.\n\n\nLet me check if there's a standard format I can reference from the repository instructions or documentation. The custom instructions mention `evaluation.yml`, `Models.cs`, and `InvestigatingResults.md`, so I should be able to provide helpful guidance on the evaluation structure and best practices.","outputTokens":722,"requestId":"5C43:1CB4B6:1BD7752:1EED31D:69FA923F"},"id":"4da7e0d2-79e9-440e-82ac-d278ac117c58","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:58:58.102Z","parentId":"5f15d836-9577-4518-af8b-dec575ce6913"}
